Privacy Policy
Last Updated: January 24, 2025
INTRODUCTION.
Welcome to Couple Joy ("we," "us," or "our"). This Privacy Policy governs the collection, use, and protection of personal information obtained from individuals ("users" or "you") who access, interact with, and use the features, functionalities, services, content, and offerings provided through our mobile application, website, sub-domains, and affiliated platforms (collectively, the "Platform"). This Privacy Policy explains the types of data we collect, how we use, store, and protect that information, and your rights regarding your personal data. By accessing or using our Platform, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
At Couple Joy, your privacy is our priority. We are committed to respecting your privacy rights and safeguarding the confidentiality and security of your personal information. We comply with all applicable privacy laws and regulations to ensure that your data is handled responsibly and transparently. If you do not agree with the practices outlined in this Privacy Policy, we kindly ask that you refrain from using our Platform.
By continuing to use the Platform, you signify your acceptance of this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection, use, storage, and disclosure of your personal data as described herein and in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. If you have any questions, concerns, or feedback about this Privacy Policy, please contact us using the information provided in the
Contact Us
section.
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices, technologies, or legal requirements. Any updates will be effective upon posting the revised Privacy Policy on our Platform. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy regularly to stay informed about how we collect, use, and protect your information.
Thank you for choosing Couple Joy. Your trust and privacy are essential to us, and we are dedicated to providing a secure and enjoyable experience on our Platform.
TYPES OF DATA WE COLLECT.
To provide the best possible experience on our Platform, Couple Joy collects various types of information from and about users. This section outlines the categories of data we collect, both directly from you and automatically through your interaction with our Platform.
Information You Provide Directly
: We collect the following information when you voluntarily provide it to us, such as during account creation or profile updates:
Name:
To identify your account and personalize your experience.
Email Address:
To facilitate account access, send communications, and provide customer support.
Profile Picture and Cover Picture:
To allow for a more personalized user profile and interaction.
Couple Anniversary Date:
To enhance app functionality and provide tailored content or features.
Information We Collect Automatically
: When you interact with our Platform, certain information is collected automatically to improve your experience, ensure security, and optimize app functionality. This includes:
Device Information:
Type of device (e.g., phone, tablet).
Operating system and version.
Unique device identifiers.
Time zone settings.
Usage Data:
Actions you take within the app (e.g., features used, duration of app sessions).
Interactions with our Platform, such as page views and button clicks.
Network and Connection Information:
IP address.
Language Preferences:
App language and phone language settings.
Location Data (Optional):
With your explicit consent, we may collect and process your precise location data to provide enhanced functionality and personalized features.
Important Notes About Location Data:
Location sharing is not mandatory and requires user opt-in.
We do not store location history. Only the last known location is stored while the account is active.
Location data may be collected in the background if permissions are granted or when specific widgets are used.
Sensitive Information:
We strive to minimize the collection of sensitive information. However, the optional collection of precise location data, as described above, may fall under this category depending on applicable laws.
Aggregate and Anonymous Data:
We may collect data in an aggregated or anonymized format that does not directly identify you. This information is used for analytics, trend analysis, and app improvement purposes.
HOW WE COLLECT DATA.
We collect data from you through various interactions with our Platform, including when you actively provide information and when it is gathered automatically as you use the app.
When you create an account or update your profile, you voluntarily provide information such as your name, email address, profile picture, cover picture, and couple anniversary date. This data is necessary to personalize your experience and ensure the functionality of the app.
In addition to the information you provide, we automatically collect certain details about your device and interactions with our Platform. For example, we gather data about your device type, operating system, app version, IP address, time zone, and language settings. We also track how you use the app, including the features you interact with and the duration of your sessions. This information is used to improve the app, develop new features, and maintain the security and stability of our systems.
If you grant permission, we may collect your precise location to enable optional, location-based features within the app. Location data is only collected with your explicit consent and is not mandatory for using our Platform. We store only the most recent location data while your account is active, and we do not retain a history of your location. This data may also be gathered in the background if you enable specific features or widgets that rely on location tracking.
The information we collect, whether provided directly by you or gathered automatically, ensures that we can deliver a secure, personalized, and high-quality experience tailored to your needs.
HOW WE USE DATA.
The information we collect is essential for providing, improving, and maintaining the functionality and quality of our Platform. At Couple Joy, we use your data responsibly and transparently to enhance your experience and ensure the security of our services. Specifically, we use your data for the following purposes:
Account Creation and Management:
To create and maintain your user account, personalize your profile, and provide access to the app’s features and functionalities.
Enhancing User Experience:
To tailor the app to your preferences, including personalized features based on the couple anniversary date and other profile details.
App Functionality:
To enable core features such as profile management and optional location-based functionalities, ensuring the app operates as intended.
Communication:
To send service-related updates, announcements, security alerts, and administrative messages necessary for maintaining your account and the app’s functionality.
Marketing and Promotions:
To share newsletters, offers, and promotional content with you. Marketing preferences are set to “ON” by default upon account creation, but you can unsubscribe at any time using the “Unsubscribe” link in emails or by contacting us directly.
App Improvement and Development:
To analyze usage patterns, monitor performance, and identify opportunities for new features and enhancements that align with user needs.
Security and Fraud Prevention:
To safeguard your data, detect unauthorized access, and protect against fraudulent activities.
We may combine the data you provide with automatically collected information to offer a seamless and optimized experience on the Platform. Rest assured, we do not use your personal data for purposes beyond those outlined in this Privacy Policy unless required by law or with your explicit consent.
NO SALE OF DATA.
We uphold the highest standards of data privacy and are committed to protecting the personal information of our users. In line with this commitment, we firmly assert that we do not engage in the sale of any user's personal data. This stance is a core element of our privacy practices and reflects our dedication to maintaining the trust and confidence of our users.
For clarity, the term "sale" of data, as used in this Privacy Policy, refers to the exchanging, transferring, or otherwise making available of a user's personal data to third parties for monetary or other valuable consideration. We understand the importance of this distinction and assure our users that their personal data will not be treated as a commodity in any business transactions.
It is important to note that this Privacy Policy does not preclude us from sharing data in ways that do not constitute a "sale" as defined above. This includes sharing information with service providers who assist us in operating our Platform, conducting our business, or serving our users, so long as these parties agree to keep this information confidential and use it solely for the purposes we have directed. Moreover, we may disclose personal data when legally required to do so, to comply with a subpoena, bankruptcy proceedings, or similar legal process, or when we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.
We prioritize transparency in all our data practices and aim to provide our users with control over their personal data. In line with this, we ensure that users are informed about the types of data we collect, the purposes for which we collect it, and the circumstances under which it might be shared, as detailed in other sections of this Privacy Policy.
This No Sale of Data policy is subject to regular review and may be updated to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. Any updates will be communicated through revisions to our Privacy Policy, and we encourage users to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect their personal information.
LAWFUL BASIS FOR COLLECTION.
At Couple Joy, we collect and process your personal data in accordance with applicable privacy laws and regulations. The lawful basis for our data collection and processing activities depends on the nature of the information and the specific context in which it is collected. We rely on the following lawful bases:
Consent:
Your consent is the foundation for many of our data collection practices. For instance, when you voluntarily provide your information during account registration or enable location tracking, you explicitly agree to the collection and use of this data for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. You can withdraw your consent at any time by adjusting your settings or contacting us, although this may limit your access to certain features of the Platform.
Contractual Necessity:
The processing of your personal data is essential for the performance of the contract between you and Couple Joy. For example, we require your data to create your account, provide access to the app, and enable its core features. Without this information, we would be unable to fulfill our contractual obligations to you.
Legitimate Interests:
We process certain data to pursue our legitimate business interests in providing a secure, high-quality, and personalized user experience. These interests include app optimization, fraud prevention, and system security. When processing your data based on legitimate interests, we ensure that your privacy rights are not overridden by our operational needs.
Legal Obligations:
In some cases, we are required to collect, retain, or disclose personal data to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal processes. For example, we may process your data to respond to a court order or government request.
User Protection:
We may process your data when necessary to protect your vital interests or the interests of others, such as ensuring the safety and security of the Platform or addressing unauthorized access.
By relying on these lawful bases, we ensure that our data collection and processing activities are conducted responsibly, transparently, and in compliance with all applicable legal requirements. If you have questions about the lawful basis for a specific data processing activity, please contact us using the details provided in the
Contact Us
section of this Privacy Policy.
HOW WE SHARE DATA.
At Couple Joy, we respect your privacy and take care to limit the sharing of your personal data. However, there are circumstances where sharing your information is necessary to operate our Platform, deliver services, or comply with legal requirements. This section outlines how and why your data may be shared.
Service Providers:
We share personal data with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in delivering, maintaining, and improving the Platform. These providers include:
-
Hosting Services:
Your data, including photos and videos, may be stored on secure platforms such as Google Cloud, Cloudflare, and Amazon Web Services.
-
Email and Communication Services:
Providers that help us send notifications, updates, and marketing emails.
These service providers are contractually obligated to handle your data securely and use it only for the purposes specified by Couple Joy.
Business Transfers:
In the event of a merger, acquisition, sale, or transfer of assets, your personal data may be shared or transferred to the acquiring entity or third parties involved in the transaction. If such a change occurs, we will notify you of the new ownership and any changes to the way your data is handled, as described in this Privacy Policy.
Compliance with Legal Obligations:
We may disclose your personal data to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal processes, such as responding to court orders, subpoenas, or government requests. This includes situations where disclosure is necessary to:
- Protect the rights, property, or safety of Couple Joy, our users, or others.
- Investigate and address fraud, security issues, or violations of our Terms of Service.
Aggregate and Anonymized Data:
We may share aggregated or anonymized information that cannot reasonably identify you with third parties for analytics, research, or marketing purposes. This type of data is used to understand trends and improve the Platform without compromising your privacy.
User-Authorized Sharing:
If you explicitly consent to or request that we share your data (e.g., integrating with a third-party service or enabling optional app features), we will do so only as authorized by you.
No Sale of Data:
As stated in the No Sale of Data section, we do not sell your personal data to third parties for monetary or other valuable consideration.
We prioritize your privacy and strive to ensure that any sharing of data is conducted responsibly, transparently, and only as necessary to operate our Platform and provide you with the best possible experience. For more details about our data practices or to withdraw consent for data sharing, please contact us using the information provided in the
Contact Us
section.
DATA SECURITY.
At Couple Joy, safeguarding your personal information is one of our highest priorities. We have implemented robust technical, administrative, and organizational measures designed to protect your data against unauthorized access, loss, misuse, alteration, or destruction. While no system can guarantee complete security, we are committed to employing industry best practices to minimize risks and ensure your data remains secure.
Security Measures We Implement:
Encryption:
Data transmitted through our Platform is protected using encryption protocols to prevent unauthorized access during transmission.
Access Controls:
Access to personal data is restricted to authorized personnel who require it to perform their job functions. These individuals are bound by strict confidentiality agreements and are trained in data protection practices.
Secure Storage:
Your data is stored on servers that adhere to strict security standards, located in facilities with controlled access and advanced monitoring.
Regular Audits:
We conduct periodic security assessments and system audits to identify vulnerabilities and strengthen our safeguards.
Backup Systems:
Hourly backups of your data are performed and retained for up to 90 days to ensure data availability and recovery in the event of system failures or unforeseen incidents.
While we take significant steps to protect your personal information, it is important to note that no system is entirely immune to security breaches. You play a critical role in maintaining the security of your data by:
Using a strong, unique password for your account.
Avoiding sharing your login credentials with others.
= Keeping your device secure and updating your operating system and apps regularly to benefit from the latest security patches.
In the unlikely event of a data breach, we have a comprehensive incident response plan in place to address and mitigate potential harm as outlined in the Section titled “Data Breach Response.” If your personal information is affected, we will notify you promptly, as required by applicable laws, and provide you with steps you can take to protect yourself further.
We are dedicated to staying ahead of emerging security threats and continuously improving our practices. We regularly update our security protocols and adapt to evolving technologies to ensure your data remains as safe as possible.
If you have any questions or concerns about how we protect your data, or if you suspect unauthorized access to your account, please contact us immediately using the details provided in the
Contact Us
section.
DATA RETENTION.
We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. The retention period for your data depends on the type of information, the reason it was collected, and applicable laws and regulations.
Account Information:
Your account data, including your name, email, profile picture, cover picture, and couple anniversary date, is retained for as long as your account remains active. Once you delete your account, all personal data is immediately removed from our primary database.
Backup Copies:
While we delete personal data from our primary database upon account deletion, backup copies may be retained for up to 90 days for system recovery and disaster management purposes. These backups are encrypted and inaccessible during normal operations.
Location Data:
If you have opted to share your location, we store only your last known location while your account is active. No historical location data is retained.
Usage Data:
Aggregated and anonymized usage data may be retained indefinitely for analytical and operational purposes, as it does not identify you personally.
In certain situations, we may be required to retain your data beyond the standard retention period to comply with legal or regulatory obligations, such as tax or audit requirements, or to address disputes or enforce agreements.
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal data at any time by deleting your account through the app (Profile > Settings > Delete Account). Once your account is deleted, we will remove your data from the primary database and cease processing it, except as necessary to fulfill legal or regulatory obligations.
We regularly review our data retention policies to ensure they align with evolving legal requirements and industry best practices. Any updates to our retention policies will be reflected in this Privacy Policy. If you have questions about how long we retain specific types of data or need assistance deleting your information, please contact us using the details provided in the Contact Us section.
CHILDREN’S PRIVACY.
Our Platform is committed to protecting the privacy of children. Consistent with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and other applicable laws and regulations, we do not knowingly collect, use, or disclose personal information from children under the age of 18.
Age Restriction: Our services are not directed to children under the specified age. We do not knowingly engage in transactions or communications with children under this age. Our Terms and Conditions prohibit users under this age from accessing our Platform and services.
Parental Consent and Involvement: If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under the specified age without parental consent, we will take steps to delete the information as soon as possible. We strongly encourage parents and guardians to take an active role in their children’s online activities and to inform us if they believe their child has provided personal information to us without their consent.
Information Collection Practices Regarding Children: In the rare event that we collect personal information from children under the specified age with parental consent, such information will be used solely for the purpose for which it was collected, and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Access and Deletion Requests by Parents or Guardians: Parents or guardians who believe that their child under the specified age has submitted personal information to our Platform can contact us to request access to, correction of, or deletion of their child’s personal data.
Commitment to Data Security: We understand the importance of safeguarding children’s privacy and security online. We implement stringent security measures to protect children's personal information and comply with relevant legal requirements pertaining to data protection and privacy.
Updates to our Children’s Privacy Policy: This policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We encourage parents and guardians to review this policy regularly.
Reporting Concerns: We take concerns about children's privacy seriously. If you have any questions or concerns about our Children's Privacy Policy or our practices concerning children’s personal data, please contact us using the information provided in the
Contact Us
section.
USER RIGHTS.
At Couple Joy, we are committed to empowering you with control over your personal data. In accordance with applicable data protection laws, you have several rights concerning the information we collect, process, and store. This section outlines your rights and explains how you can exercise them.
Right to Access:
You have the right to request confirmation of whether we process your personal data and, if so, to access that data. Upon request, we will provide you with a copy of the personal data we hold about you, along with details about how it is used and shared.
Right to Rectification:
If any of your personal information is inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated, you have the right to request that we correct or update it. You can also edit certain information directly within the app, such as your name, email, profile picture, and user-generated content.
Right to Deletion:
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal data. If you choose to delete your Couple Joy account through the app (Profile > Settings > Delete Account), all associated data will be permanently removed from our primary database. Backup copies of your data may be retained for up to 90 days for disaster recovery purposes, but these backups are securely stored and inaccessible during regular operations.
Right to Restrict Processing:
You may request that we limit the processing of your data in specific circumstances, such as if you contest the accuracy of the data or object to its processing. During the restriction period, we will store your data but not process it further, except as required by law.
Right to Data Portability:
You have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format. If technically feasible, you may also request that we transfer this data directly to another service provider of your choice.
Right to Object:
You may object to the processing of your data in certain cases, such as when data is processed for direct marketing purposes. If you object, we will cease processing your data for those purposes unless we have compelling legitimate grounds to continue or are required to do so by law.
Right to Withdraw Consent:
Where we rely on your consent to process your data, you have the right to withdraw that consent at any time. Withdrawing consent will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
Right to Lodge a Complaint:
If you believe that your rights have been violated, you have the right to file a complaint with the relevant data protection authority. We encourage you to contact us first so we can address your concerns directly.
You can exercise your rights by contacting us through the information provided in the Contact Us section of this Privacy Policy. We may request verification of your identity to ensure the security and privacy of your data. Please note that some requests may be subject to legal or contractual restrictions or may require us to retain certain data for compliance purposes. We are committed to responding to your requests in a timely and transparent manner. If you have questions or need further assistance, don’t hesitate to reach out to us.
GDPR Compliance: Couple Joy complies with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) for users located in the European Union. Under GDPR, you have the following rights in addition to those outlined in the User Rights section:
Right to Be Informed: You have the right to know how your personal data is collected, processed, and used, as explained in this Privacy Policy.
Right to Erasure ("Right to Be Forgotten"): You can request that we delete all your personal data under specific circumstances, such as when it is no longer needed for the purposes for which it was collected.
Right to Restrict Processing: If you contest the accuracy of your personal data or object to its processing, you can request restricted processing until the matter is resolved.
International Transfers: We implement safeguards, such as Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs), for transferring data outside the EU to ensure your data is handled securely and in compliance with GDPR.
CPA Compliance: Couple Joy complies with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) for users located in California. Under CCPA, California residents have the following rights in addition to those outlined in the User Rights section:
Right to Know: You have the right to request details about the personal information we collect, including the categories of data collected, the purposes for collection, and any third parties with whom it is shared.
Right to Opt-Out: While we do not sell personal information, you have the right to opt out of the sale of your personal data if that changes in the future.
Right to Deletion: You can request the deletion of your personal information, subject to certain exceptions, such as compliance with legal obligations.
Non-Discrimination: We will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights under CCPA, including denial of services or changes in pricing or quality.
